prototypes.description: Electronics and software used to receive and distribute commands and to store and forward payload data and spacecraft telemetry.
Radio and associated hardware, such as cabling and antennas, used to communicate with the ground or other spacecraft.
Sensors and software necessary to control the spacecraft orbit (Position and Orbit Determination and Control)
Electronics, power generation, and power storage devices, as well as harnessing for power distribution.
Spacecraft thrust, including fuel storage and plumbing
All the hardware that supports the spacecraft, including the primary structural components, brackets, fasteners, and the actuators and mechanisms associated with the deployed or movable structures.
All the hardware necessary to control the temperature of the spacecraft.
